Healing from anything often feels this way. If you are like me, you tend to get caught up in the frustration of having to take the steps backwards, and lose sight of the blessings found in the step forward. I impatiently cry out against the forces preventing me from leaping forward... I want to heal quickly. 

Healing is never a fast process. Mentally, emotionally, and physically recovering from a trauma takes time.  We need to allow ourselves the grace and patience to slow down and not lose sight of the progress we are making. To continue to find the beauty in the hard journey, to celebrate the successes and gains even if they are painfully slow. 

