....
Second promised post in our series of ways to immediately change and take control of your life/career.
....
Has something ever happened that just totally upset you and you immediately lashed out/shut down/lied/ran away/did something you totally regretted?  We've ALL been there.  When we get in the moment, we make mistakes.  We're human like that.  And unfortunately sometimes we lose out on great opportunities because of our imperfections.
...
Sometimes people mistakenly believe that the way to avoid this is to turn off our emotions entirely and reject them.  If you don't feel, then you don't react poorly, right?  Unfortunately, no.  In fact this is very wrong.  The reason being that this extreme position will still lead to poor reactions because while we might avoid sudden anger outbursts or other similar things, we will also miss out on the opportunity to react in a state of pure honesty.  If you act like you aren't hurt when you are hurt, you remain damaged.  If you act like you aren't happy when you're actually stoked, someone might not realize how happy you make them.  Or what a perfect fit you are for an opportunity.
...
The key here is to allow yourself to FEEL what you feel.  Whatever the emotion is, allow it to rise up within you and show itself.  Then, before you do anything about that feeling, give it a good look.  Acknowledge it without judgment.  Allow it to be present.  Once you've done that, you gain control of it.  Then YOU get to decide what to do with it before it spills over onto someone or something else.
...
You can't master the emotions you've shut out or can't feel.  If you fail to acknowledge them, they will inevitably control you.
...
Self mastery is a journey.  It'll take time.  Be patient with yourself and remember the last post about failure and mistakes.  Keep your eye on the goal, and even failure becomes productive.  Comment your thoughts below :)
.
.
.
